  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of essential health services to populations most affected by drought in 4 districts of Western and Southern provinces</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide essential health services to populations in priority drought-affected districts. WHO will use CERF funds to roll-out an electronic surveillance platform, support maternal and perinatal death surveillance and response, train rapid response teams, and implement events-based surveillance. 279,037 people will benefit from this project (including 64,564 women and 75,792 girls), which will be implemented in 6 months.</narrative>
  </description>
